result.name: Coyote Bar & Grill

reviews.text: Great for company's parties, food,drinks and lots of fun.... Bachelors parties... Engagement or Divorce parties:))))

My go to place for good guacamole and nachos. They serve table side guac to you taste with a great selection, I personally like extra bacon corn and minimum peppers. Also make decent margaritas at the bar. Comfortable setting and good service, but it's all wee pricey. Come for an occasion, not regularly.
Great Mexican food, fast service, cold beers

The food was very good and a welcome break from eating Chinese every meal. The prices were high and the portions not very large, and of course we only saw Chinese employees, no Mexicans. They had a DJ playing music and the music videos were playing on large screens. The downstairs area is a bar and upstairs is more like a sit-down restaurant although it overlooks the bar downstairs. We got a happy hour discount on margeritas from 5pm-8pm, but a pitcher still cost 55 USD.

Coyote is a bar and grill on Lockhart Road in Wanchai. This is a pretty good place for Mexican food during the day and for party atmosphere in the evenings. Opening hours are 12pm to 2am daily. 

Here you find a cantina with table seating wrapped around an oval shaped bar. Decor is similar to many Tex-Mex restaurants in the States. Menu is an expected range of enchiladas, burrito, taco, nacho and other related dishes. Prices are on the high side for Wanchai but serving sizes are generous and food has tasted pretty good when I've eaten here in the past. 

During a recent lunch, I had the grilled chicken enchilada (HK$190) served with chili sauce and smothered with guacamole, sour cream and served with Mexican rice. The rice wasn't great but the enchilada was just fine, plenty filling as well. 

In the end, a good place if you want your Mexican food fix while in the Wanchai area. With a round of drinks, be ready to spend around HK$250-275 (US$32-35) per person at Coyote.
